ERROR:ASSIGN_IN_IF: do not use assignment in if condition
#106: FILE: drivers/i2c/i2c-core.c:729:
+		if ((res=client->driver->detach_client(client)))

Do not use assignments in if condition.
Example::

  if ((foo = bar(...)) < BAZ) {

should be written as::

  foo = bar(...);
  if (foo < BAZ) {

WARNING:SPLIT_STRING: quoted string split across lines
#108: FILE: drivers/i2c/i2c-core.c:731:
+			dev_err(&adapter->dev, "detach_client failed for "
+				"client [%s] at address 0x%02x\n",

Quoted strings that appear as messages in userspace and can be
grepped, should not be split across multiple lines.

See: https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20120203052727.GA15035@leaf/

WARNING:EXPORT_SYMBOL: EXPORT_SYMBOL(foo); should immediately follow its function/variable
#128: FILE: drivers/i2c/i2c-core.c:1303:
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(i2c_remove_device);

EXPORT_SYMBOL should immediately follow the symbol to be exported.

CHECK:AVOID_EXTERNS: extern prototypes should be avoided in .h files
#141: FILE: include/linux/i2c.h:363:
+extern int i2c_probe_device(struct i2c_adapter *adapter, int driver_id,

Function prototypes don't need to be declared extern in .h
files.  It's assumed by the compiler and is unnecessary.

